    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation to the author's intent in its original context and the psalm's place in the canonical whole. Psalm 70 is five verses, but its theological compression rewards careful pericope-by-pericope analysis. Three movements trace the psalm's argument: the opening cry of urgency, the imprecatory and doxological center, and the return to personal petition.",
